6.12	The_Way_Home	The Way Home (2002 film)	The Way Home is an award-winning 2002 film written and directed by Lee Jeong-hyang. It tells the heart-warming story about a grandmother and her city-born grandson who comes to live with her in a rural village. The film, which reminds the younger generation of the unconditional love and care that old people selflessly give, won South Korea's equivalent of the Oscars for best picture and screenplay.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/5c/The_Way_Home_film.jpg/220px-The_Way_Home_film.jpg
